text: Kingman Reef is a coral reef in the North Pacific Ocean, owned by the United States."Kingman Reef" at CIA World Factbook ; excerpt, "no indigenous inhabitants"; retrieved 2013-4-19. It is the farthest north of the Northern Line Islands. It is only sometimes above water. Palmyra Atoll is the other U.S. territory in the Northern Line Islands. == Gallery == Image:Orthographic projection over Kingman Reef.png|Orthographic projection over Kingman Reef.
